    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/3–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate General</gloss> at Jerusalem</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 9, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Please explain to Khalidi the following points and urge him to reconsider
                    decision mentioned in <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 271, March 8:<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d86fn1">Not printed; but see footnoted, <ref target="#pg_687"
                            >p. 687</ref>.</note>
                    <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>The US Govt’s interpretation of the <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                            resolution is that it refers to peaceful implementation;</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Under <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> resolution consultations
                            envisaged are informal and between the Big 5, who may wish to inquire
                            attitudes of people of Palestine on situation there. Therefore, <gloss
                                target="#t_AHC1">AHC</gloss> should not be unduly concerned with
                            reference to implementing resolution of <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                                >GA</gloss>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Understand Nakhleh telephoning Cairo to request permission to participate in
                    informal consultations and hope your representations to <gloss target="#t_AHC1"
                        >AHC</gloss> will convince them of great desirability in Arabs’ own interest
                    in these consultations.</p>
                <p>Sent to Jerusalem as 172; repeated to Cairo as 279; Baghdad as 74; Jidda as 70;
                    Beirut as 99; and Damascus as 52. <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> as
                    128.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
